a wrapper for react-perfect-scrollbar. always use this component as scrollbar

Parameters:
Name Type Attributes Description
props.direction "left" | "right" | "reverse" <optional>

determines whether the scrollbar should be placed at left or at right the default direction for RTL mode is 'left' and for LTR mode is 'right' if you set the 'direction' equal to 'reverse', the scollbar will be placed at the opposite side of default direction
props.brightMode boolean <optional>

set this to true when the scrollbar in placed on a dark background
props.className string <optional>

extra class name for scrollbar container
props.scrollEndOptions.top boolean <optional>

if equal to 'true', scroll end will be calculated based on top of container
props.scrollEndOptions.offset number <optional>

the offset in pixels to check if scroll is near the end
props.scrollEndOptions.onEndReach event <optional>

handler of the scroll-end event
